21struct objdump_private_option
22{
23 /* Option name. */
24 const char *name;
25
26 /* TRUE if the option is selected. Automatically set and cleared by
27 objdump. */
28 unsigned int selected;
29};
30
31struct objdump_private_desc
32{
33 /* Help displayed for --help. */
34 void (*help)(FILE *stream);
35
36 /* Return TRUE if these options can be applied to ABFD. */
37 int (*filter)(bfd *abfd);
38
39 /* Do the actual work: display whatever is requested according to the
40 options whose SELECTED field is set. */
41 void (*dump)(bfd *abfd);
42
43 /* List of options. Terminated by a NULL name. */
44 struct objdump_private_option *options;
45};
46/* ELF32_AVR specific target. */
47extern const struct objdump_private_desc objdump_private_desc_elf32_avr;
48
49/* XCOFF specific target. */
50extern const struct objdump_private_desc objdump_private_desc_xcoff;
51
52/* Mach-O specific target. */
53extern const struct objdump_private_desc objdump_private_desc_mach_o;
